cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.IR 

This paper discusses a meta-algorithm for fuzzy graph clustering, which has applications in natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves computational analysis and machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of clustering for sense and frame induction, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
